cs.NI, cs.IT, cs.SY, cs.MM, cs.DC 

Reasoning: 
1. cs.NI (Networking and Internet Architecture) - The paper discusses power control in a two-tier cellular network, which falls under the domain of networking and internet architecture. 
2. cs.IT (Information Theory) - The paper derives a fundamental relation for the largest feasible cellular Signal-to-Interference-Plus-Noise Ratio (SINR), which involves information theory concepts. 
3. cs.SY (Systems and Control) - The proposed distributed utility-based SINR adaptation at femtocells involves control theory concepts. 
4. cs.MM (Multimedia) - The paper discusses link budget analysis, which is relevant to multimedia systems. 
5. cs.DC (Distributed, Parallel, and Cluster Computing) - The proposed algorithm for reducing transmission powers of the strongest femtocell interferers involves distributed computing concepts.
